claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Header page of an MMWR (Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report) document, showing title, series information (Recommendations and Reports / Vol. 71 / No. 1), and date (August 26, 2022). The image only displays the report title and publication information and contains no data on Flublok antigen content or immunogenicity; it does not support the claim. Note: Image is limited to header text; no relevant clinical or antigen content data are present.
